== 制作 ==
{{Quote|text=韩流现象已席卷全球，BLACKPINK可以说是世界上最受认可、最热门的女子组合。导演卡罗琳·徐与Jisoo、Jennie、Rosé和Lisa四人的可信赖关系，促成了许多有机且真实的时刻，让观众可以真实地了解BLACKPINK的生活，以及她们面对每首热门单曲、历史性的表演及卖座演唱会时所做的奉献和艰辛的准备。我们很高兴能为她们全世界的粉丝呈现她们的故事。|author=亚当·德·迪奥（Adam Del Deo），Netflix纪录片副总裁<ref name=deadline/>|title=|source=}}

影片由凭借Netflix系列纪录片《{{le|星厨烹饪法门|Salt Fat Acid Heat}}》获[[艾美奖|艾美奖]]提名的卡罗琳·徐导演，卡拉·莫斯制片，{{tsl|en|RadicalMedia|RadicalMedia}}执行制作<ref>{{cite web|title=Blackpink|url=https://www.radicalmedia.com/work/blackpink|website=RadicalMedia|accessdate=2020-10-04|archive-date=2020-11-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125013533/https://www.radicalmedia.com/work/blackpink|dead-url=no}}</ref>。此前，Netflix一直在跟BLACKPINK合作，打造首个韩流项目，于是就把这个计划介绍给卡罗琳<ref>{{cite web|last1=Boone|first1=John|title=BLACKPINK Wanted 'Everything to Be Real' in Their Netflix Documentary (Exclusive)|url=https://www.etonline.com/blackpink-netflix-documentary-director-caroline-suh-154650|website=Entertainment Tonight|accessdate=2020-10-14|date=2020-10-14|archive-date=2020-11-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201126051632/https://www.etonline.com/blackpink-netflix-documentary-director-caroline-suh-154650|dead-url=no}}</ref>。影片分两次拍摄，第一次于2019年秋季进行，第二次于[[2019冠状病毒病疫情|2019冠状病毒病疫情]]全球流行前的2020年2月进行。BLACKPINK练习生生涯的画面由组合的经纪公司[[YG娱乐|YG娱乐]]提供<ref>{{cite web|last1=Miller|first1=Shannon|title=Director Caroline Suh on Netflix's BLACKPINK doc Light Up The Sky: "I hope this humanizes them"|url=https://news.avclub.com/director-caroline-suh-on-netflixs-blackpink-doc-light-u-1845354329|website=AV Club|accessdate=2020-10-14|date=2020-10-13|archive-date=2020-10-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201031164537/https://news.avclub.com/director-caroline-suh-on-netflixs-blackpink-doc-light-u-1845354329|dead-url=no}}</ref>。卡罗琳希望影片“能够赋予BLACKPINK每个成员人性的一面，让人们把她们看作立体的人，而不是单纯的偶像”<ref>{{cite web|last1=Tangcay|first1=Jazz|title=‘Blackpink: Light Up the Sky’ Director Caroline Suh on Charting the Rise of Korea’s Biggest Girl Band|url=https://variety.com/2020/music/news/blackpink-documentary-interview-director-netflix-caroline-suh-1234802161/|website=Variety|accessdate=2020-10-14|date=2020-10-14|archive-date=2020-11-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201117045520/https://variety.com/2020/music/news/blackpink-documentary-interview-director-netflix-caroline-suh-1234802161/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

在影片的全球新闻发布会上，Rosé表示片名《照亮天空》是她们在录音棚录歌时起的，是歌曲《[[How_You_Like_That|How You Like That]]》的歌词<ref>{{cite web|last1=Bueno|first1=Seven|title=Blackpink and Director Caroline Suh ‘Light Up the Sky’|url=https://mb.com.ph/2020/10/14/blackpink-and-director-caroline-suh-light-up-the-sky/|website=Manila Bulletin|accessdate=2020-10-14|date=2020-10-14|archive-date=2020-10-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201015093245/https://mb.com.ph/2020/10/14/blackpink-and-director-caroline-suh-light-up-the-sky/}}</ref>。

==宣传==
2020年9月8日，Netflix和BLACKPINK分别在社交媒体宣布影片的首映日期<ref>{{cite tweet|title=BLACKPINK: Light Up the Sky — an all-access documentary about one of the world's most popular groups — premieres in your area on October 14! Oh and that's not all ... on October 14, these music icons will also become Netflix profile icons|number=1303483259121139712|user=netflix|accessdate=2020-10-04|date=2020-09-08}}</ref>。官方预告片于10月5日在Netflix的YouTube频道及其他社交媒体帐号公布<ref>{{cite news|last1=Rowley|first1=Glenn|title=Watch Blackpink 'Light Up the Sky' in First Trailer For Netflix Documentary|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/9460908/blackpink-light-up-the-sky-trailer-netflix|accessdate=2020-10-14|work=Billboard|date=2020-10-06|archive-date=2021-01-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210109154312/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/9460908/blackpink-light-up-the-sky-trailer-netflix|dead-url=no}}</ref>。受2019冠状病毒病疫情影响，影片的全球发布会于10月13日在[[首尔|首尔]]和[[纽约|纽约]]两地以视频通话模式进行，首尔方面由BLACKPINK主持，纽约方面由卡罗琳·徐主持<ref>{{cite news |last1=Choi |first1=Ji-won |title=Blackpink unveiled: Netflix documentary searches beyond the spotlight |url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20201014000799 |accessdate=2020-10-14 |work=The Korea Herald |date=2020-10-14 |archive-date=2020-11-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201129051701/http://www01.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20201014000799 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。10月14日影片发布当天，Netflix上线了BLACKPINK成员主题用户头像<ref name=pitchfork/>。

==专业评价==
《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》的娜塔莉亚·温克尔曼（Natalie Winkelman）认为影片是一部“出色的纪录片，凸显每位成员的个性”，“勾勒出她们当练习生时面临的艰辛，以及如今成为国际巨星所遭受的压力和孤独”，但批评影片没有“深入探讨YG工业化生产并商业化年幼人才的方式”<ref name = nytimes/>。《{{tsl|en|The Ringer (website)|The Ringer}}》的凯特·哈利威尔（Kate Halliwell）称赞影片导演“塑造了最强的韩流刻板印象，弄清楚潜藏在这个组合及四名独特女性背后的真相”<ref name=ringer/>。《[[IndieWire|IndieWire]]》的凯特·埃布兰（Kate Erbland）认为影片“充满吸引力、有趣”，“直观地介绍了”BLACKPINK及对她们成名“所付出代价的深入见解”，但没有过多着墨于韩流的另一面，缺乏对“‘练习生’生涯的深入探讨”<ref>{{cite news|last1=Erbland|first1=Kate|title=‘Blackpink: Light Up the Sky’ Review: Netflix Documentary Offers Intimate Intro to K-Pop’s Biggest Girl Group|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2020/10/blackpink-light-up-the-sky-review-netflix-documentary-kpop-1234592170/|accessdate=2020-10-14|work=IndieWire|date=2020-10-13|archive-date=2020-11-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201122203804/https://www.indiewire.com/2020/10/blackpink-light-up-the-sky-review-netflix-documentary-kpop-1234592170/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

